NAME
       cervus_meminfo - report kernel physical memory usage

SYNOPSIS
       #include <sys/cervus.h>

       int cervus_meminfo(cervus_meminfo_t *out);

DESCRIPTION
       Fills *out with a snapshot of the buddy allocator state:

           uint64_t total_bytes;   total usable RAM
           uint64_t free_bytes;    total_bytes - used_bytes
           uint64_t used_bytes;    pages currently allocated through
                                   pmm_alloc (counter-based)
           uint64_t usable_bytes;  alias of total_bytes
           uint64_t page_size;     usually 4096

       used_bytes is the difference of two atomic counters incremented
       on every pmm_alloc / pmm_free, and therefore reflects exactly
       what the kernel has handed out, not what the buddy free lists
       show.

RETURN VALUE
       0 on success, -1 on error (errno EFAULT).

SEE ALSO
       sysmon(1), meminfo(1)
